          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Sudan was discussed at London</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/khartoum-sudan-army-paramilitary-clashes-power-struggle.png" alt="Smoke rises over the city as the army and paramilitaries clash in a power struggle in Khartoum, Sudan" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Smoke rises over the city as the army and paramilitaries clash in a power struggle in Khartoum, Sudan. Credits: Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Senior diplomats and aid officials from over a dozen countries met in London to address <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-h2-4-sudans-civil-war" target="_blank">Sudan‚Äôs civil war</a>, which has entered its third year. Notably, no Sudanese representatives were present at the talks. The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-h2-5-london-conference" target="_blank">London Conference</a> focused on two main issues: a $590M humanitarian aid pledge and an urge for an immediate ceasefire. The EU and African Union officials emphasized that the aid would fall short if the conflict persisted and urged for renewed international diplomacy and engagement.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Meanwhile, the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) paramilitary leader, Mohamed Hamdan Dagalo, declared that he would create a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-h2-6-rival-government" target="_blank">rival government</a>, the Government of Peace and Unity. He said his government would be federal, non-centralized, and have a "unified, professional, apolitical military." Dagalo also promised education, health, and justice for the entire nation.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The conflict in the region stems from a power struggle between Sudan‚Äôs army chief and the leader of the Rapid Support Forces. This struggle has caused the world‚Äôs largest displacement crisis. Currently, 13 million people are forced from their homes, and 25 million face extreme hunger.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
