        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">EU to rescue the Palestinian Authority</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The EU has announced an aid package for the Palestinian Authority. </strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The European Union has announced a ‚Ç¨1.6B ($1.8B) aid package for the Palestinian Authority. This <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-h3-7-funding-will-support" target="_blank">funding will support</a> development projects in the West Bank, Gaza Strip, and East Jerusalem. Over a third of the package will go directly to budget support to enhance economic sustainability, governance, and services that help private sector growth.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The aid package is broken as follows:<p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">‚Üí</span>‚Ç¨576M ($652M) to fund projects across key sectors like healthcare</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">‚Üí</span>‚Ç¨80M ($90.9M) allocated towards UNRWA.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">‚Üí</span>Up to ‚Ç¨400M ($412M) in low-interest credits will be available for Palestinian businesses</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The announcement comes as Israel intensified its offensive in Gaza, including a strike on Al-Ahli Hospital. Israel said they targeted a Hamas command center in the hospital.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hamas recently rejected an <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-h3-8-egyptian-proposed-ceasefire" target="_blank">Egyptian-proposed ceasefire</a> plan that included a 45-day truce and the release of half of the Israeli hostages in the first week. The agreement also called for the entry of humanitarian aid into Gaza. However, Hamas objected to the condition that Palestinian factions disarm, calling disarmament non-negotiable.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
