          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá≠üá∫ Hungary‚Äôs parliament votes to limit the rights of dual nationals and LGBTQ+ people</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Hungary's parliament <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-br1-9-approved-constitutional-amendments" target="_blank">approved constitutional amendments</a> that limit LGBTQ+ rights and affect dual citizens, leading to widespread protests. The government, led by Viktor Orban‚Äôs Fidesz party, asserts the changes protect children‚Äôs development, allowing bans on public LGBTQ+ events and suspending citizenship for dual nationals deemed security threats. The law is suspected of targeting figures like George Soros.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Critics called it a step toward authoritarianism. Opposition MP David Bedo warned that the laws threaten all types of protest, not just Pride events. A law banning pride marches was introduced last month, with PM Viktor Orban vowing to block "woke ideology."</p>
        </mj-text>
