          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∑üá∫ Russian general ousted after criticizing military top brass to return to battle</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Once a respected Russian commander, Major General Ivan Popov returned to the front lines after being dismissed and jailed for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-16-04-2025-br2-10-criticizing-military-leadership" target="_blank">criticizing military leadership</a>. This time, he will lead the ‚ÄúStorm Z‚Äù unit, a penal battalion of ex-convicts used in high-risk assaults.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">In 2023, Popov accused top officials of sabotaging his forces and was later arrested for alleged fraud, a charge he denies. Analysts see this as a dangerous assignment, with some calling it a ‚Äúdeath sentence.‚Äù Popov had previously appealed to Putin for a return to duty. While supporters see his reinstatement as redemption, it‚Äôs also viewed as a political maneuver.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
